# Testing rules

- Test observable behavior, state transitions, invariants, and failure paths.
- Prefer domain unit tests, application tests with fakes, adapter contract tests, and a small number of boundary integration tests.
- Make tests deterministic: freeze time, seed randomness, and isolate network and provider dependencies.
- Name tests by behavior and condition; use arrange–act–assert structure.
- Add regression coverage for every defect fix.
- Never weaken assertions or skip tests merely to obtain a passing run.
